   <mods:abstract>The deponent, 78 years old, at sea since his sixteenth year, knows how to
            calculate latitude. According to his computations, the northern part of Sandy Hook is in
            the latitude 40 degrees 25'. The forestaff, which has been in use as long as he can
            remember, is employed by both Dutch and French for observing latitude at sea. He does
            not know whether it agrees with David Quadrant. As far as he knows, sixty miles make up
            a degree of latitude. The difference in latitude between Sandy Hook and the Fort at New
            York is 20 or 21 miles on a northern course. Signed, Jacob Early. In Jay's
            hand.</mods:abstract>
